With the Africa Women’s Cup of Nations (AWCON) starting in Morocco, Saturday, Super Falcon’s Group C opponent Banyana Banyana of South Africa have been told to be wary of Barcelona’s top striker Asisat Oshoala. According to Banyana’s poster girl Thembi Kgatlana, the Nigerian girls are the team to beat, and Oshoala is the player to look forward to. The champions will kick off their campaign against South Africa on Monday against South Africa. Other teams in the group are Botswana and Burundi.   Calabar Port roars back to life after three years of…     Drogba: Osimhen can be ‘best striker in the…     Tanzania side, Azam unveil Plateau United’s Ndala   Super Falcons are hot favourites to retain the title as 11-time AWCON champions and have always been there in the finals. Nigeria played two friendlies against highly ranked opponent Canada to prepare for the tournament. The first game ended 2-0 in favour of Canada, who’re sixth in the FIFA rankings, while the second tie was a 2-all stalemate in April. Nigeria qualified for the finals in Morocco by beating Ivory Coast in the final qualifying round. Banyana finished as runners-up five times in the past but believed the time is ripe for them to deliver. All eyes will be on Kgatlana, who won the Player of the Tournament and the leading scorer gongs, at the last edition in Ghana in 2018.